**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Make/Model:** Not specified (only the rear bumper is visible)

**Location of Damage:**
- The rear bumper of the vehicle shows signs of impact damage.
- There are visible scratches and dents on the surface of the bumper.

**Type of Damage:**
- The damage appears to be from an external impact, likely caused by another vehicle or object.
- The scratches and dents suggest that the bumper has been hit, possibly at a low angle, causing the paint to chip and the metal to dent.

**Additional Notes:**
- No other visible damage is apparent on the portion of the vehicle shown in the image.
- The damage seems localized to the rear bumper area.

**Recommendation:**
- Inspect the rest of the vehicle for any additional hidden damage before finalizing the assessment.
- Schedule repairs if necessary, focusing on the rear bumper area where the damage is located.

Please note that this assessment is based solely on the visible portion of the vehicle in the provided image. Further inspection may be required to determine the full extent of the damage.
